xGeometry></mxCell><mxCell id="e4" value="charge humans for the meat they eat" style="edgeStyle=none;curved=1;html=1;endArrow=block;endFill=1;strokeColor=#9aa6b3;fontSize=9;fontColor=#5b6675;strokeColor=#8a5fb0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="w1_2_6" target="w1_2_6_7"><mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"><Array as="points"><mxPoint x="156" y="861"/><mxPoint x="145" y="908"/></Array></mxGeometry></mxCell><object label="Animals count&lt;br&gt;(neuron-weighted)&lt;br&gt;[1+2]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;(Peter Singer, Lewis Bollard)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Farmed vertebrates enter the circle, weighted by a sentience-adjusted welfare range (neuron-count exponent). Corporate welfare campaigns avert enormous suffering per dollar and overtake human global health under most welfare-range estimates. An animals person won&#x27;t think only people in their community matter, so this assumption requires far_away_humans. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx1lW9T4zYQxr%2FKTqadJkwIjg%2FKXTp5kYD5M5frMVzamw5mQLHXsXqy5JHkGJfju3dlB5KQ5BUmu%2Fppd%2FU80nMrxoQVwp6pGFuD1tERDIdDmGrGJVgFkWb%2FVfRRSggL3%2BsfQ6m0iBccSyj7Dz60jVU5%2BB23LJS0fGRMkeWWKwlRSpQBeJAzraKUM%2BEg%2FU8%2B9CFh%2BoGVrHpIi4xJ8xrwgUmeMWEejMqwTJmtoQGLUmArMjfA4KayKX0nXCBQtauwOQJLK4HFsemCRmqRSzSgdA3TeEgFsQwtam7od5tiU%2BtvBpJCRjXjD4hUlivD5XyVQGtljESkn7ipacYyGTOhJEJGMxQ9eHwbUbB4dKW65fiUY2Rp4YKJAkElNWE1zV4NG6OxMCsqKNw2bqHB9cYGMCXWlRsZwgTZvMBm4WXwZ3A7mgbnMKtgjhI1s9jLq9dTw5jbjQkdULALUtmmDjdEItWsc66pVMAkcX9owuimr%2FScxpNrOh1dwYy2SHjE6bsL4%2BDi621A7WsmakKJfJ5amhwNQyino5Q%2FNocm1FwqTScMn7xf4ewa2kpTq4cqOczYXHJbxAjjr9PgrEP1GFXkn7mNUpTnTFQ3qP8yMQzhOZQAOapc4BWKHOO3iNfzTtyGXu%2FE5ZQoxAypkks6PYdoUrx%2Bk%2BP1XVKkCklaSFhkCybGTP74uz4kl%2Fphz04HO9AH0O7D4T5cJ5QvoZzHG424WrzjZTGeH0qWJVsJH5YdeT6Vy3i2lfDajU8921RsxPs930WPT2maZb4Z8j3PxU6PqYhQllzEs2JuNnN%2Bb3I%2B%2BnUOEyLB7Rb8t5GTN0ql3mfUcUfwlhoL7srz0eQfYAvUzhU5qf2X%2B8G61OINGVqeLZ26klmkKEgiRGnfuYmWs3f3EOSFNU7N3DphRcq5eAh37nyfgeaOAwhbExWRNJ3s4Eeju7DVhTJ%2Ba2cAGTLZ3inMDimgDy%2FdTeQlX2BjKVHthq1rYj%2FjO%2BkN3GVL7WhuK2iPvlx0dhM3VLQbObr%2BAkdwtmQF0mrM6XbDQpuU53uw69rbjd26n3aTNlTqSM633snpx23it5TunByofXozEG60%2BpdmuedY1hVeY7dw30nl9FwYYhhop02pOd27JKQYzZ6BbntjN300mVwE53um9847ewjXYFiC7nxvGy%2FBLb0CTEfpntq2LLcC3zu7abqB3Cs2hAk3tqeRPGewXf9jlLbjqt3YoQvPP59%2BwlNvbY%2BXDt1bM%2FcsDWEJuvPuly6e7nzYplfX31ZWHIB7xcl1BmavrxuZnFMVhoy49lbSDi5jffdQtl7%2BB0w46yU%3D" id="w1_2"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#e6e2c0;strokeColor=#b0a04a;fontColor=#3a3410;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="136" y="0" width="236" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Future humans count&lt;br&gt;(discounted)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;▼ 87 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Future people are inside the circle, but with a positive pure-time discount rate — the moderate longtermist position. A modest discount is enough to keep present, measurable global health competitive with future-protecting work; remove it (the next assumption) and the astronomical numbers take over. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_3.drawio" id="w1_2_3"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f2e3b3;strokeColor=#c9a72a;fontColor=#57450e;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="27" y="239" width="172" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;▼ 19 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5.drawio" id="w1_2_5"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f5d3b8;strokeColor=#cc7a33;fontColor=#5a300e;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="73" y="478" width="200" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Suffering-focused&lt;br&gt;ethics&lt;br&gt;[1+2+6]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;(Brian Tomasik, David Pearce)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + suffering_focused&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Asymmetry: averting intense suffering takes priority over creating happiness. Factory farming, malaria and the worst wild-animal conditions weigh up; speculative future-flourishing bets weigh down. Arises most naturally from taking animal suffering seriously, so it requires animals_somewhat. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 6 suffering_focused" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJx9lW1z4jYQx7%2FKDtNOIUOIcZ56dHgBifMw5XqZHO1NJ2SIsNdYPVnySHIcN5fv3pUNAQL0VRx29dun%2F0qvjQhjlgt7oSJs9BpHR9Dv92GsGZdgFYSa%2FVvSRyFhkvte9wQKpUX0zLGAojv1p2fQNFZlcNZyByeSAANj8jSzXEkIE%2BL0wIOMaRUmnAmH6X7yoQsx01N